1
00:00:30,438 --> 00:00:34,113
All right, Coop.
A hundred and five degrees.

2
00:00:34,198 --> 00:00:38,635
- What do you say?
- 105? I can go more.

3
00:00:39,958 --> 00:00:42,677
107.

4
00:00:43,478 --> 00:00:46,948
- 108.
- I'm feeling it.

5
00:00:47,038 --> 00:00:48,676
109.

6
00:00:48,758 --> 00:00:50,953
OK, the suspense is killing me.

7
00:00:51,038 --> 00:00:52,391
- All right, 110.
- 110?

8
00:00:52,478 --> 00:00:55,151
- 110.
- A hundred and ten toasty ones.

9
00:00:55,238 --> 00:00:57,388
Right. Ready to go out
and greet the heat?

10
00:00:57,478 --> 00:00:58,957
The warm wind in my hair?

11
00:00:59,038 --> 00:01:00,551
- Are you ready?
- I'm ready.

12
00:01:00,638 --> 00:01:02,435
- Let's do it.
- Let's do it.

13
00:01:14,478 --> 00:01:16,309
Thirty-one. Thirty-one degrees.

14
00:01:16,398 --> 00:01:19,390
- Thirty-one below.
- Thirty-one below! New record!

15
00:01:19,478 --> 00:01:21,469
- Thirty-one below!
- New record!

16
00:01:21,558 --> 00:01:24,630
New record! Oh, it's cold!

17
00:02:37,518 --> 00:02:39,236
I hate to do this, but...

18
00:02:39,318 --> 00:02:41,513
Rise and shine, kids.
No more sleeping in.

19
00:02:46,078 --> 00:02:49,036
All right.
If "rise and shine" won't work...

20
00:02:49,118 --> 00:02:50,756
Is anybody hungry this morning?

21
00:02:52,798 --> 00:02:54,231
Attaboy, Max.

22
00:02:55,518 --> 00:02:58,271
What do you say?
Ready for exercise before breakfast?

23
00:02:59,438 --> 00:03:01,633
How you doing?

24
00:03:01,718 --> 00:03:03,071
How does right field look?

25
00:03:03,958 --> 00:03:07,394
I think it looks pretty good.
What do you say, Max? Here we go.

26
00:03:07,478 --> 00:03:09,116
Go get it!

27
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:14,637
Hey, Maya.

28
00:03:15,558 --> 00:03:17,150
How's my best girl doing?

29
00:03:18,438 --> 00:03:20,349
How you doing?

30
00:03:20,438 --> 00:03:22,076
You keeping everybody in line?

31
00:03:23,358 --> 00:03:26,031
Left field. Go get it.

32
00:03:26,118 --> 00:03:28,154
Left field, Maya. Here we go.

33
00:03:29,398 --> 00:03:30,717
Go get it!

34
00:03:33,438 --> 00:03:35,190
Attaboy, Max. Come here, buddy.

35
00:03:42,438 --> 00:03:45,157
Settle down.
There's plenty to go around, guys.

36
00:03:45,238 --> 00:03:46,671
Here you go, Shorty.

37
00:03:47,798 --> 00:03:49,151
Good boy, Shadow.

38
00:03:49,238 --> 00:03:52,548
Dewey. Truman.

39
00:03:52,638 --> 00:03:53,832
There you go, Old Jack.

40
00:04:08,678 --> 00:04:11,636
That's my best girl.
Here, I'll trade you.

41
00:04:11,718 --> 00:04:12,628
There you go, Maya.

42
00:04:27,078 --> 00:04:29,273
- Hi.
- Hey.

43
00:04:29,358 --> 00:04:32,316
- Didn't think I'd see you this year.
- Guess you got lucky.

44
00:04:32,398 --> 00:04:33,797
- I guess so.
- Crazy Katie!

45
00:04:33,878 --> 00:04:37,632
- Did you get your pilot's license yet?
- Oh, Coop, I missed you.

46
00:04:37,718 --> 00:04:38,946
OK.

47
00:04:42,638 --> 00:04:44,993
- Got that?
- Yeah.

48
00:04:45,078 --> 00:04:46,557
Hey, hey, careful with that.

49
00:04:46,638 --> 00:04:50,392
That equipment's made it 10,000 miles.
I'd hate that to change in six feet.

50
00:04:50,478 --> 00:04:52,150
Sorry about that.

51
00:04:52,238 --> 00:04:54,593
Hi. I'm Dr Davis McClaren.

52
00:04:54,678 --> 00:04:56,589
Earth and Space Sciences UCLA.

53
00:04:56,678 --> 00:05:00,717
Jerry Shepard, expedition guide.
Welcome to the bottom of the world.

54
00:05:00,798 --> 00:05:02,390
- Nice to meet you.
- Same here.

55
00:05:02,478 --> 00:05:05,311
Go any further south,
you'll fall off the planet.

56
00:05:05,398 --> 00:05:07,548
Well, that'd be unfortunate.

57
00:05:07,638 --> 00:05:11,313
Charlie Cooper, cartographer,
mechanical engineer, runway paver.

58
00:05:11,398 --> 00:05:14,196
- Nice to meet you.
- Dr McClaren! Welcome to the ice.

59
00:05:14,278 --> 00:05:17,429
Andy Harrison, NSF science director.
An honour to meet you.

60
00:05:17,518 --> 00:05:20,590
- Dr Rosemary Paris, field coordinator.
- Nice to meet you.

61
00:05:20,678 --> 00:05:21,747
You've met our team?

62
00:05:21,838 --> 00:05:24,910
Yeah, Mr Cooper was just taking
good care of all my things.

63
00:05:24,998 --> 00:05:27,637
Cooper? First time
for everything, I suppose.

64
00:05:27,718 --> 00:05:29,436
- Let's get you inside.
- Thanks.

65
00:05:29,518 --> 00:05:32,271
- Sure.
- Yeah.

66
00:05:35,758 --> 00:05:38,397
OK. Lady luck, in my corner.

67
00:05:38,478 --> 00:05:41,117
- What are we playing?
- She is pretty.

68
00:05:41,198 --> 00:05:43,348
- Quarter in.
- Quarter.

69
00:05:43,438 --> 00:05:45,906
- You're going down.
- You're going down.

70
00:05:45,998 --> 00:05:47,750
Crazy Katie, you're going down.

71
00:05:47,838 --> 00:05:50,147
- Hey, doc, you want in?
- No, thanks.

72
00:05:50,238 --> 00:05:52,035
I gave up gambling a long time ago.

73
00:05:52,118 --> 00:05:54,313
Hey, you flew in with Katie, didn't you?

74
00:05:54,398 --> 00:05:56,787
Remind me how you're getting home.

75
00:05:59,558 --> 00:06:01,514
Say, Old Jack, you in or out, buddy?

76
00:06:03,558 --> 00:06:06,152
- Translation?
- That'd be out.

77
00:06:07,638 --> 00:06:10,550
So, Coop, how's the new girlfriend?

78
00:06:11,478 --> 00:06:12,513
How's my new girl?

79
00:06:13,358 --> 00:06:14,393
I don't know.

80
00:06:15,358 --> 00:06:17,633
- How about hot?
- Wow.

81
00:06:18,198 --> 00:06:19,995
Wow.

82
00:06:20,078 --> 00:06:22,797
She's a scientist too.
At the Italian base.

83
00:06:22,878 --> 00:06:24,357
- Pretty and smart.
- Smarts.

84
00:06:24,438 --> 00:06:26,872
Notice something missing
in that picture?

85
00:06:26,958 --> 00:06:30,394
OK, OK. I think...
I know you mean me.

86
00:06:30,478 --> 00:06:34,073
You're talk... Picture's coming.
She's sending one of the two of us.

87
00:06:34,158 --> 00:06:35,147
Patience, Jer.

88
00:06:35,238 --> 00:06:37,388
- How many?
- Two.

89
00:06:37,478 --> 00:06:40,390
Doc, looking forward
to your first trip to Dry Valleys?

90
00:06:40,478 --> 00:06:42,708
It's a pretty cool spot
this time of year.

91
00:06:42,798 --> 00:06:45,437
Actually, Dr McClaren
needs to get to Mt Melbourne

92
00:06:45,518 --> 00:06:47,588
to search for his meteorite.

93
00:06:49,998 --> 00:06:51,636
Melbourne?

94
00:06:51,718 --> 00:06:53,834
Nobody said anything about Melbourne.

95
00:06:53,918 --> 00:06:56,512
Yeah. Meteorite hunting
is a pretty small world

96
00:06:56,598 --> 00:06:59,271
and I didn't want anybody
to know where I was going,

97
00:06:59,358 --> 00:07:02,555
cos I'm looking
for something special at Melbourne

98
00:07:02,638 --> 00:07:05,232
and the NSF let us
keep it off the paperwork.

99
00:07:06,878 --> 00:07:08,152
Is there a problem?

100
00:07:09,278 --> 00:07:11,712
Look, doc, let me show you something.

101
00:07:15,238 --> 00:07:17,274
I'll show you on the map.

102
00:07:18,038 --> 00:07:20,108
- This is where we are, right? OK.
- Yeah.

103
00:07:20,198 --> 00:07:21,517
Here's Dry Valleys.

104
00:07:21,598 --> 00:07:25,637
All the way over here, Mt Melbourne.
Twice as far and the opposite direction.

105
00:07:25,718 --> 00:07:28,186
I've been over our route twice
in the last week,

106
00:07:28,278 --> 00:07:31,714
but I haven't been to Mt Melbourne
since the beginning of the season.

107
00:07:31,798 --> 00:07:34,596
That may be so. But
Dr McClaren has travelled a long way.

108
00:07:34,678 --> 00:07:37,954
- If we can accommodate him, we should.
- It's the end of January.

109
00:07:38,038 --> 00:07:40,996
The ice is thin and snowmobiles
would be too dangerous.

110
00:07:41,078 --> 00:07:43,831
There's only one way
to make that trip, with the dogs.

111
00:07:43,918 --> 00:07:45,874
The dogs?

112
00:07:47,038 --> 00:07:50,235
OK. Will they be able
to carry all my gear?

113
00:07:50,318 --> 00:07:52,229
The dogs'll be fine.

114
00:07:52,318 --> 00:07:55,151
- It's late in the season.
- Last year we had the dogs out

115
00:07:55,238 --> 00:07:57,627
right up until the day we left.

116
00:08:00,638 --> 00:08:03,869
All right, Andy.
You're the boss. I'll get things ready.

117
00:08:06,158 --> 00:08:10,037
- Hey, you need some help?
- No, I'm fine.

118
00:08:10,118 --> 00:08:11,631
Coop, say good night to Buck.

119
00:08:13,558 --> 00:08:16,595
I'm gonna take a rain check, Jer.

120
00:08:20,158 --> 00:08:21,876
Kids, come on! Let's go!

121
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:24,995
Everyone outside. Let's get you
tucked into bed. Come on.

122
00:08:32,358 --> 00:08:34,189
Good, Jack.

123
00:08:34,278 --> 00:08:36,348
Good boy. I'll see you in the morning.

124
00:08:39,718 --> 00:08:41,549
Hey, Maya.

125
00:08:43,118 --> 00:08:44,915
What do you say? One more trip?

126
00:08:44,998 --> 00:08:48,274
Then we'll get you to McMurdo
for the winter. That sound good?

127
00:08:48,998 --> 00:08:51,512
That sound good? That's my girl.

128
00:08:53,718 --> 00:08:57,393
Hey, Max. I need a good trip out of you.

129
00:09:01,278 --> 00:09:03,553
Lucky star, huh? Let's hope so.

130
00:09:04,398 --> 00:09:06,116
See you in the morning, Max.

131
00:09:12,878 --> 00:09:14,027
Knock, knock.

132
00:09:14,118 --> 00:09:15,631
- Hey.
- Hey.

133
00:09:15,718 --> 00:09:18,073
I warmed up some of
your favourite ice cream.

134
00:09:18,158 --> 00:09:20,877
Strawberry.
That's your favourite ice cream.

135
00:09:20,958 --> 00:09:24,030
Well, you got here early.
I didn't have time to go shopping.

136
00:09:25,558 --> 00:09:28,470
Yeah, well, they changed things up.

137
00:09:28,558 --> 00:09:30,116
How you been?

138
00:09:30,198 --> 00:09:32,268
Been a good season.
Kids are doing well.

139
00:09:32,358 --> 00:09:35,748
Maya's been awesome.
Old Jack's getting a bit older, so...

140
00:09:35,838 --> 00:09:38,227
Jerry, I was asking you how you've been.

141
00:09:43,598 --> 00:09:45,714
I'm not interrupting or anything, am I?

142
00:09:45,798 --> 00:09:47,789
No, Rosie. We were just catching up.

143
00:09:48,358 --> 00:09:50,235
OK.

144
00:09:52,878 --> 00:09:55,187
All right, well...

145
00:09:55,278 --> 00:09:57,473
I guess I'll see you guys
in the morning.

146
00:09:57,558 --> 00:09:59,116
Thank you. That was sweet.

147
00:10:00,478 --> 00:10:02,548
No problem. Good night.

148
00:10:02,638 --> 00:10:04,515
Good night.

149
00:10:14,638 --> 00:10:16,788
- Pardon me.
- Oh, sorry.

150
00:10:20,158 --> 00:10:22,114
Head's up.

151
00:10:22,878 --> 00:10:26,871
Sad fact of life in this place, doc.
Floor is more comfy than the bunks.

152
00:10:26,958 --> 00:10:29,552
So, what is it exactly that you do here?

153
00:10:29,638 --> 00:10:33,950
Cartography. I spent the last two years
mapping every inch of this territory.

154
00:10:35,598 --> 00:10:37,793
Hey, dude.
What happened? You strike out?

155
00:10:41,358 --> 00:10:43,349
No. I didn't even swing.

156
00:10:44,398 --> 00:10:47,788
Went down looking.
That's still a strike-out, Jer.

157
00:10:50,518 --> 00:10:52,076
Sorry about that, buddy.

158
00:10:52,158 --> 00:10:53,876
I didn't see you there.

159
00:10:58,358 --> 00:11:02,192
We turn the heat off at night, so if
there's anything you need to keep warm,

160
00:11:02,278 --> 00:11:03,711
I suggest you sleep with it.

161
00:11:06,358 --> 00:11:07,473
Incoming.

162
00:11:08,558 --> 00:11:10,150
Jerry!

163
00:11:10,558 --> 00:11:12,230
Man!

164
00:11:18,238 --> 00:11:19,990
OK, this is the last of it.

165
00:11:25,118 --> 00:11:28,030
Wow, doc.
Won't be losing you, now, will we?

166
00:11:30,158 --> 00:11:31,876
All right, rule number one.

167
00:11:31,958 --> 00:11:35,348
If you want to approach the dogs,
approach them from the front.

168
00:11:35,438 --> 00:11:37,269
- See how the lines are taut?
- Yeah.

169
00:11:37,358 --> 00:11:40,873
I want them like that at all times.
If the line's tangled, they'll fight.

170
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:42,391
- We don't want that.
- Got it.

171
00:11:42,478 --> 00:11:45,515
- Anything else I should know?
- The rest is pretty much up to me.

172
00:11:45,598 --> 00:11:47,475
Gotta watch them. They're working.

173
00:11:47,558 --> 00:11:49,913
They'll run themselves to death.
They love work.

174
00:11:49,998 --> 00:11:52,512
All right, official introductions.

175
00:11:52,598 --> 00:11:55,635
Up here in front, on lead,
we got my best girl, Maya.

176
00:11:55,718 --> 00:11:57,629
Next to her we got Old Jack.

177
00:11:57,718 --> 00:12:01,347
Just turned ten, and he's
actually getting ready for retirement.

178
00:12:01,438 --> 00:12:04,111
Back here,
the white one, this is Shorty.

179
00:12:04,198 --> 00:12:06,837
And next to him is the pup
of the bunch. That's Max.

180
00:12:06,918 --> 00:12:08,397
He's still in training.

181
00:12:08,478 --> 00:12:11,311
He's got the right stuff.
I expect big things out of him.

182
00:12:11,398 --> 00:12:13,707
Right here, we got the twins.
This is Truman.

183
00:12:13,798 --> 00:12:16,358
Truman took a bite
out of Dewey a couple years ago.

184
00:12:16,438 --> 00:12:18,952
- Notice the scar above Dewey's eye?
- Oh, yeah.

185
00:12:19,038 --> 00:12:22,587
Yeah. Well, they've been
buddies ever since, so...

186
00:12:22,678 --> 00:12:25,476
Back here, last but not least,
we got the two malamutes.

187
00:12:25,558 --> 00:12:28,675
The grey one's Shadow
and the red one's his buddy, Buck.

188
00:12:28,758 --> 00:12:31,750
All brawn and absolutely no brain.
But we love 'em.

189
00:12:33,678 --> 00:12:36,351
- Everyone good to go this morning?
- Yeah, I think so.

190
00:12:36,438 --> 00:12:38,827
I was just being introduced
to Maya, Old Jack,

191
00:12:38,918 --> 00:12:41,386
Shorty, Max, Truman,
Dewey, Shadow and Buck.

192
00:12:41,478 --> 00:12:43,355
- Excellent.
- Jer?

193
00:12:44,558 --> 00:12:47,834
- Be careful out there, OK?
- Always.

194
00:12:47,918 --> 00:12:49,237
Take care of Cooper for me.

195
00:12:49,318 --> 00:12:51,832
Don't worry. I'll give him
plenty of food and water.

196
00:12:51,918 --> 00:12:53,317
OK, enough. Are we done?

197
00:12:53,398 --> 00:12:57,391
I'd like a picture of our
intrepid explorers, please. Thank you.

198
00:12:57,478 --> 00:12:59,628
All right. Hang on!

199
00:12:59,718 --> 00:13:01,197
OK.

200
00:13:01,278 --> 00:13:02,267
OK, you ready?

201
00:13:03,958 --> 00:13:06,472
<i>Uno, dos, tres.</i>

202
00:13:07,398 --> 00:13:09,434
Handsome. So handsome.

203
00:13:10,118 --> 00:13:13,030
Hey, Coop. You'd better get up here
and say goodbye to Buck.

204
00:13:15,918 --> 00:13:18,068
Oh, yeah?

205
00:13:18,158 --> 00:13:20,718
All right, see you, Buck!

206
00:13:20,798 --> 00:13:22,709
Safe... Safe trip, Buck.

207
00:13:22,798 --> 00:13:25,710
Come over and say goodbye.
You're gonna give him a complex.

208
00:13:29,118 --> 00:13:31,188
And what about my complex?

209
00:13:31,278 --> 00:13:33,428
Come around... Come say goodbye to him.

210
00:13:35,518 --> 00:13:38,954
I'm... I'm pretty sure he heard me
say goodbye, Jer. I don't...

211
00:13:40,038 --> 00:13:42,393
OK. I don't know why you do this.

212
00:13:43,838 --> 00:13:45,954
OK.

213
00:13:47,238 --> 00:13:48,717
See ya, Buck.

214
00:13:48,798 --> 00:13:50,754
All right. You...

215
00:13:50,838 --> 00:13:54,797
You take care of the doctor
and Jerry, OK?

216
00:13:56,838 --> 00:13:58,749
Nasty!

217
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:00,191
That was disgusting!

218
00:14:00,278 --> 00:14:03,350
I got dog spit all in my mouth
and my nose!

219
00:14:04,318 --> 00:14:05,512
It's not funny.

220
00:14:08,718 --> 00:14:11,357
I don't see what's so funny.

221
00:14:11,958 --> 00:14:14,836
All right.
Take care, guys. We'll see you.

222
00:14:14,918 --> 00:14:16,397
- Bye.
- See ya.

223
00:14:16,478 --> 00:14:19,151
All right, team!
Last hike of the season!

224
00:14:19,238 --> 00:14:20,717
Let's go! Hike! Hike!

225
00:14:49,838 --> 00:14:51,954
Come on, Jack! Come on, Old Jack!

226
00:14:52,038 --> 00:14:54,347
Let's go, Maya! Come on, girl!

227
00:15:24,998 --> 00:15:27,466
Whoa! Whoa!

228
00:15:30,918 --> 00:15:33,478
Whoa! Whoa!

229
00:15:39,198 --> 00:15:40,711
What's the problem?

230
00:15:40,798 --> 00:15:44,586
We got ice fields up ahead.
I don't know how thick the ice is.

231
00:15:44,678 --> 00:15:47,146
That's why we couldn't take
the snowmobiles. Look.

232
00:15:47,238 --> 00:15:48,990
So, what do we do?

233
00:15:50,198 --> 00:15:51,950
I'm gonna change things up.

234
00:15:52,038 --> 00:15:54,347
Put the dogs
in a fan formation for safety.

235
00:15:54,438 --> 00:15:57,555
It's a little slower,
but it spreads the weight out.

236
00:15:57,638 --> 00:15:59,947
That way if one of the dogs
falls through the ice,

237
00:16:00,038 --> 00:16:03,826
the lead's long enough
so the rest don't follow.

238
00:16:03,918 --> 00:16:05,829
Hike!

239
00:16:35,158 --> 00:16:37,228
Hey, doc.

240
00:16:37,318 --> 00:16:39,912
- You see that over there?
- What is that?

241
00:16:41,278 --> 00:16:43,269
Here.

242
00:16:45,718 --> 00:16:47,436
You see 'em?

243
00:16:47,518 --> 00:16:50,078
- I see 'em. What are they?
- Leopard seals.

244
00:16:50,158 --> 00:16:52,274
More leopard than seal, if you ask me.

245
00:16:52,358 --> 00:16:54,872
- Give 'em a wide berth?
- Yeah, we'll give 'em space.

246
00:17:15,318 --> 00:17:16,910
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

247
00:17:16,998 --> 00:17:19,148
Whoa, kids! Whoa!

248
00:17:20,118 --> 00:17:22,586
- What was that?
- We're on a glacier now.

249
00:17:22,678 --> 00:17:24,953
We're gonna have to
take her slow, doc. Get off.

250
00:17:25,038 --> 00:17:28,872
I want you to take the brake.
You're gonna run the sled. All right?

251
00:17:28,958 --> 00:17:30,676
Heavy brake.

252
00:17:30,758 --> 00:17:33,352
Follow my footprints.
Keep the sled on my footprints.

253
00:17:33,438 --> 00:17:34,791
- I'll probe ahead.
- Got it.

254
00:17:34,878 --> 00:17:38,075
This glacier's always moving,
so we have to be careful.

255
00:17:42,918 --> 00:17:46,115
All right, doc. Keep two feet
on the brake if you need to.

256
00:17:46,198 --> 00:17:49,110
- Just keep a steady go, all right?
- All right.

257
00:17:49,198 --> 00:17:51,758
All right, kids, come on! Easy, now!

258
00:17:51,838 --> 00:17:54,113
Nice and easy. Let's go.

259
00:18:14,198 --> 00:18:16,234
All right, stop! Stop!

260
00:18:16,318 --> 00:18:18,548
All right, hard brake, right there!

261
00:18:20,798 --> 00:18:22,675
We got a crevasse right here.

262
00:18:22,758 --> 00:18:26,671
I'm not sure how big it is,
so we're gonna go around. OK.

263
00:18:26,758 --> 00:18:29,955
We're gonna bring it over this way.
Slow and easy.

264
00:18:30,038 --> 00:18:31,630
I'm gonna call Maya over,

265
00:18:31,718 --> 00:18:34,835
and then I just want you
to let up ever so lightly, all right?

266
00:18:34,918 --> 00:18:37,990
- All right, got it.
- All right, Maya, haw! Haw!

267
00:18:41,038 --> 00:18:43,598
Haw! Haw!

268
00:18:43,678 --> 00:18:45,111
Max, what are you doing?

269
00:18:46,118 --> 00:18:47,153
Max, no. Haw!

270
00:18:48,238 --> 00:18:50,547
Max! Stop! Stop, Max! Doc, stop!

271
00:18:52,838 --> 00:18:54,510
No!

272
00:18:59,878 --> 00:19:01,311
Hold on, doc!

273
00:19:03,838 --> 00:19:06,750
Doc! Put both hands on the sled!
Both hands on the sled, doc!

274
00:19:09,598 --> 00:19:12,795
Hike! Come on, Jack, take it home!

275
00:19:12,878 --> 00:19:15,438
Come on, Maya, take her home!

276
00:19:16,958 --> 00:19:18,027
Come on! Hike!

277
00:19:35,798 --> 00:19:37,595
Oh, man!

278
00:19:37,678 --> 00:19:38,713
You OK?

279
00:19:39,678 --> 00:19:41,589
Yeah.

280
00:19:51,718 --> 00:19:53,276
Do me a favour.

281
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:57,556
Next time you decide to go to Melbourne,
don't pack so much stuff.

282
00:19:57,638 --> 00:19:59,913
And try coming a bit earlier.

283
00:19:59,998 --> 00:20:02,466
Andy said the trip was fine.
You agreed to go.

284
00:20:06,438 --> 00:20:09,111
Andy's my boss. I do what he says.

285
00:20:09,198 --> 00:20:12,588
If you didn't think it was safe,
you shouldn't have backed down.

286
00:20:27,918 --> 00:20:30,512
Easy.

287
00:20:36,518 --> 00:20:38,588
Jerry, thanks for today.

288
00:20:39,158 --> 00:20:42,628
Yeah. No problem.

289
00:20:48,278 --> 00:20:50,394
Who's the artist?

290
00:20:50,478 --> 00:20:53,276
My son, Eric.

291
00:20:54,598 --> 00:20:56,668
He does one every trip.

292
00:20:59,918 --> 00:21:01,909
He looks like your wife.

293
00:21:01,998 --> 00:21:04,353
Lucky kid.

294
00:21:07,078 --> 00:21:08,830
Yeah.

295
00:21:08,918 --> 00:21:11,193
What about you?
You got somebody?

296
00:21:11,278 --> 00:21:12,347
Are you kidding me?

297
00:21:12,438 --> 00:21:15,555
I'm here six months a year
dragging scientists around.

298
00:21:15,638 --> 00:21:17,754
What kind of woman
would put up with that?

299
00:21:17,838 --> 00:21:20,716
How about Katie?
Looked like you might've had something.

300
00:21:20,798 --> 00:21:24,791
Yeah. A couple years ago we did.

301
00:21:24,878 --> 00:21:28,029
You know how it goes. Sometimes
it works, sometimes it doesn't.

302
00:21:28,118 --> 00:21:30,678
I guess relationships
don't fit my lifestyle.

303
00:21:33,038 --> 00:21:35,074
Anyhow, come on. Let's go outside, guys.

304
00:21:35,158 --> 00:21:38,548
We're gonna get an early start tomorrow.
Come on. Come on, Max.

305
00:21:38,638 --> 00:21:40,913
Come on, Max.

306
00:22:03,958 --> 00:22:05,437
All right, whoa!

307
00:22:05,518 --> 00:22:08,191
Hold it. Put on the brake,
I'm gonna take it from here.

308
00:22:08,278 --> 00:22:11,270
Yeah, got it. Whoa!

309
00:22:13,718 --> 00:22:15,629
What do you say?

310
00:22:15,718 --> 00:22:18,391
- That's something else.
- That's Melbourne.

311
00:22:19,358 --> 00:22:23,271
- That's your home for the next week.
- Beautiful.

312
00:22:23,358 --> 00:22:25,394
Ready, now! Hike!

313
00:22:37,958 --> 00:22:42,509
<i>Victoria, this is McMurdo Weather.</i>
<i>Come in.</i>

314
00:22:42,598 --> 00:22:45,510
<i>Victoria? This is McMurdo Weather.</i>

315
00:22:45,598 --> 00:22:47,873
This is Victoria. We copy you, Mactown.

316
00:22:47,958 --> 00:22:51,587
<i>Hi, Andy. It's Steve.</i>
<i>Just checking status on your team.</i>

317
00:22:51,678 --> 00:22:54,238
We've got four at the base
and two in the field. Over.

318
00:22:54,318 --> 00:22:56,115
<i>Suggest you bring them in.</i>

319
00:22:56,198 --> 00:22:58,871
<i>We have two massive</i>
<i>low pressure systems moving south.</i>

320
00:22:58,958 --> 00:23:02,428
<i>Control wants you in early</i>
<i>just to be safe. Over.</i>

321
00:23:02,518 --> 00:23:04,429
Copy that, Mactown. Over and out.

322
00:23:04,518 --> 00:23:06,634
Get Jerry on the radio.

323
00:23:17,798 --> 00:23:20,107
Wanna sling me a cup of that
when you get a chance?

324
00:23:20,198 --> 00:23:21,950
Yeah, sure thing.

325
00:23:28,038 --> 00:23:30,154
- You got her?
- Yeah, thanks.

326
00:23:33,358 --> 00:23:34,837
How's that looking there?

327
00:23:34,918 --> 00:23:38,035
Well, everything points
to the spot that we're on.

328
00:23:38,118 --> 00:23:41,474
The next couple days
are gonna tell us a lot.

329
00:23:41,558 --> 00:23:43,549
<i>Field base to Melbourne. Come in.</i>

330
00:23:44,558 --> 00:23:47,072
<i>Base to Melbourne. Come in.</i>

331
00:23:48,878 --> 00:23:50,072
<i>Jerry?</i>

332
00:23:50,158 --> 00:23:52,114
<i>Jerry, do you read me? Over.</i>

333
00:23:52,198 --> 00:23:54,473
Yeah, go for Melbourne. That you, Katie?

334
00:23:54,558 --> 00:23:56,992
<i>Jerry, we got a call from Mactown.</i>

335
00:23:57,078 --> 00:24:00,150
<i>... major storm coming in. Over.</i>

336
00:24:00,238 --> 00:24:03,036
You'll have to go again.
We're in a bad spot here.

337
00:24:03,118 --> 00:24:07,031
<i>Jerry... back to field base.</i>
<i>Do you copy?</i>

338
00:24:07,118 --> 00:24:11,509
<i>We got a major storm coming in.</i>
<i>Mactown wants you in right away. Over.</i>

339
00:24:11,598 --> 00:24:13,828
All right. Copy that. We'll be back.

340
00:24:13,918 --> 00:24:15,829
When do we expect this storm?

341
00:24:17,598 --> 00:24:18,713
Katie?

342
00:24:23,358 --> 00:24:25,713
Sorry. Looks like
we're gonna have to pack up.

343
00:24:25,798 --> 00:24:30,235
- Well, when do we have to leave?
- We leave first thing, tomorrow.

344
00:24:54,398 --> 00:24:56,707
- Listen, Jerry...
- You heard what she said.

345
00:24:56,798 --> 00:25:01,349
Now, Jerry, look. I cannot
go back without at least trying.

346
00:25:01,438 --> 00:25:02,996
Well, that's not your call.

347
00:25:04,118 --> 00:25:05,949
No. It's not.

348
00:25:06,038 --> 00:25:08,029
There's a major storm coming in.

349
00:25:08,118 --> 00:25:10,074
Not a minor one, but a major.

350
00:25:10,158 --> 00:25:12,672
Down here there's a big difference
between the two.

351
00:25:12,758 --> 00:25:15,511
My job as your guide
is to get you back home in one piece,

352
00:25:15,598 --> 00:25:17,316
and that's what I'm gonna do.

353
00:25:17,398 --> 00:25:20,708
But Jerry, we're talking
about a rock from another world.

354
00:25:20,798 --> 00:25:25,110
This ice floe might give us the first
meteorite from the planet Mercury.

355
00:25:25,198 --> 00:25:27,758
That could lead us
to discoveries we can't imagine.

356
00:25:27,838 --> 00:25:29,954
When you climb a mountain,
go up a river,

357
00:25:30,038 --> 00:25:34,316
the exciting part isn't what you know
is there. It's what you don't know.

358
00:25:34,398 --> 00:25:37,947
It's what you might find,
and it's the same here.

359
00:25:38,038 --> 00:25:41,951
I came halfway around the world to look
for something that's important to me.

360
00:25:42,038 --> 00:25:44,188
Jerry, please, you...

361
00:25:46,198 --> 00:25:48,837
You gotta take chances
for the things you care about.

362
00:25:53,318 --> 00:25:55,229
Half the day on the east slope.

363
00:25:55,318 --> 00:25:58,037
But I want to be back
on that sled tomorrow by noon.

364
00:25:58,118 --> 00:26:00,871
I'll take that. I'll take that.

365
00:26:51,958 --> 00:26:53,869
No.

366
00:27:21,398 --> 00:27:23,514
Hey, we're running
out of time here, doc.

367
00:27:23,598 --> 00:27:25,714
Believe me, I know.

368
00:27:53,158 --> 00:27:55,035
Hey, Jerry.

369
00:27:56,398 --> 00:27:59,196
- I think we got something here.
- Hey, wait, doc!

370
00:27:59,278 --> 00:28:01,348
Doc, wait a minute. Doc, don't move.

371
00:28:01,438 --> 00:28:03,076
You're outside the safety zone.

372
00:28:03,158 --> 00:28:06,275
This is a big one.
Eleven centimetres across, fully intact.

373
00:28:06,358 --> 00:28:09,270
It looks like a basalt,
but it's like nothing I've ever seen.

374
00:28:09,358 --> 00:28:11,553
- Jerry!
- Doc! Doc, don't move.

375
00:28:11,638 --> 00:28:14,596
That area's unchecked.
I told you to stay inside the flags.

376
00:28:14,678 --> 00:28:16,714
Oh, my God. This is it!

377
00:28:16,798 --> 00:28:18,231
Great, doc. Stay still.

378
00:28:18,318 --> 00:28:21,390
I'm glad you found your rock,
but let's get you out of there.

379
00:28:21,478 --> 00:28:24,868
Just follow your footsteps out.
Step right in your footprints.

380
00:28:26,718 --> 00:28:29,915
Man, I knew I could find it!
What'd I tell you? This is it.

381
00:28:29,998 --> 00:28:32,466
Half a day! Thank you.

382
00:28:32,558 --> 00:28:35,152
Now that you scared the hell out of me,
can we go home?

383
00:28:35,238 --> 00:28:38,150
- Yeah.
- All right. Let's go.

384
00:28:39,838 --> 00:28:43,353
<i>Victoria, this is Mactown. Come in.</i>

385
00:28:43,438 --> 00:28:45,349
Victoria here. We copy you, Mactown.

386
00:28:45,438 --> 00:28:48,908
<i>The approaching storm</i>
<i>has picked up speed and intensity.</i>

387
00:28:48,998 --> 00:28:52,149
<i>We are sending you the coordinates.</i>
<i>Mactown out.</i>

388
00:28:52,238 --> 00:28:54,957
Copy that, Mactown.
Over and out.

389
00:28:55,038 --> 00:28:57,074
Field base to Melbourne. Come in.

390
00:29:12,238 --> 00:29:15,310
Whoa. Whoa! Whoa, whoa, whoa!

391
00:29:15,398 --> 00:29:18,196
Whoa! Easy there, team! Easy.

392
00:29:18,278 --> 00:29:19,677
What's up?

393
00:29:19,758 --> 00:29:22,067
I got to do a patch job
on one of the kids.

394
00:29:22,158 --> 00:29:24,547
Radio Katie.
See what's going on with that storm.

395
00:29:24,638 --> 00:29:25,627
All right.

396
00:29:27,998 --> 00:29:30,990
Shoot. Looks like it's Old Jack.

397
00:29:31,078 --> 00:29:32,750
Come here, Jack.

398
00:29:33,598 --> 00:29:37,147
Field base, come in.

